rist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-06-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-06-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-06-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-06-1365x2048.jpg 1365w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1706px) 100vw, 1706px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1706\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-07.jpg\" alt=\"In this apartment, neutral tones and organic materials take center stage in the living room. Filtered sunlight washes over a minimalist sofa, sculptural wood tables, and a layered jute rug, creating a space that feels both serene and elemental.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-07.jpg 1706w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-07-940x1411.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-07-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-07-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-07-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-07-1365x2048.jpg 1365w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1706px) 100vw, 1706px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eArched windows cast a diffused glow across the space, emphasizing the organic curve of the ceiling and the earthy plaster walls. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1706\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-08.jpg\" alt=\"Arched windows cast a diffused glow across the space, emphasizing the organic curve of the ceiling and the earthy plaster walls. \" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-08.jpg 1706w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-08-940x1411.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-08-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-08-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-08-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-08-1365x2048.jpg 1365w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1706px) 100vw, 1706px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis tranquil bedroom pairs clay-toned plaster walls with a wood bed frame and an integrated vanity. The arched mirror and ceiling echo the organic curves of the architecture, while neutral linens and natural textures invite calm.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1706\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-09.jpg\" alt=\"This tranquil bedroom pairs clay-toned plaster walls with a wood bed frame and an integrated vanity. The arched mirror and ceiling echo the organic curves of the architecture, while neutral linens and natural textures invite calm.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-09.jpg 1706w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-09-940x1411.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-09-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-09-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-09-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tulum-luxury-apartment-interior-living-room-220525-1255-09-1365x2048.jpg 1365w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1706px) 100vw, 1706px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eBabel is more than architecture, it’s a statement in rose-colored concrete, offering a vision of design that nurtures instead of disrupts. When you’re next in Tulum, skip the beach resort and seek out the tower where light, shadow, and jungle converge.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003chr/\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by Conie Suárez, AlberStudio, and Daniel Villanueva | Office: V Taller | Architects: Daniel Villanueva and Miguel Valverde | Civil Works: MAQTE Company and Bramah Developments\u003c/h6\u003e\n\t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
